<div id="v470.28.1"><span class="G1161 s">In the end</span><span class="G4521 s"> G3796 of the sabbath</span><span class="G2020 s">, as it began to dawn</span><span class="G1519 s"> toward</span><span class="G3391 s"> the first</span><span class="G4521 s"> <i>day</i> of the week</span><span class="G2064 s">, came</span><span class="G3137 s"> Mary</span><span class="G3094 s"> Magdalene</span><span class="G2532 s"> and</span><span class="G243 s"> the other</span><span class="G3137 s"> Mary</span><span class="G2334 s"> to see</span><span class="G5028 s"> the sepulchre</span>.</div>
<div id="v470.28.2"><span class="G2532 s">And</span><span class="G2400 s">, behold</span><span class="G1096 s">, there was</span><span class="G3173 s"> a great</span><span class="G4578 s"> earthquake</span><span class="G1063 s">: for</span><span class="G32 s"> the angel</span><span class="G2962 s"> of the Lord</span><span class="G2597 s"> descended</span><span class="G1537 s"> from</span><span class="G3772 s"> heaven</span><span class="G4334 s">, and came</span><span class="G617 s"> and rolled back</span><span class="G3037 s"> the stone</span><span class="G575 s"> from</span><span class="G2374 s"> the door</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G2521 s"> sat</span><span class="G1883 s"> upon</span><span class="G846 s"> it</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (was: or, had been)</span></div>
<div id="v470.28.3"><span class="G1161 s">†</span><span class="G846 s"> His</span><span class="G2397 s"> countenance</span><span class="G2258 s"> was</span><span class="G5613 s"> like</span><span class="G796 s"> lightning</span><span class="G2532 s">, and</span><span class="G846 s"> his</span><span class="G1742 s"> raiment</span><span class="G3022 s"> white</span><span class="G5616 s"> as</span><span class="G5510 s"> snow</span>:</div>
